<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,1376,1619]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1449,1475]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Ecology.</emphasis>
Apart from one record from a park, all other Portuguese records originate from riverbanks and mountainous sites. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hydrophorinae" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[307,554,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hydrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balticus">
<emphasis box="[307,554,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Hydrophorus balticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected in very large numbers in boggy sites and near seeps on a mountainous slope in the eastern Pyrenees (Pollet unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,1376,1619]" box="[199,456,1556,1583]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
